  "knowledge_greg-judy_03_signals-worth-encoding": {
    "category": "grazing-management",
    "content": "- Rumen fill helps indicate whether animals were allocated enough feed. - If cattle eagerly enter a new paddock and settle into a normal grazing pattern, allocation may be close to right. - If they show poor interest in the new break, yesterday's allocation may have been too generous. - If they continue acting hungry well after the move, yesterday may have been too tight.",
    "created_at": "2026-04-13T04:19:38.815733",
    "embedding_id": "knowledge_greg-judy_03_signals-worth-encoding",
    "entry_type": "signal",
