  "knowledge_joel-salatin_02_actionable-lessons": {
    "category": "grazing-management",
    "content": "- Ruminants can lead a sequence and poultry can follow behind for sanitation and nutrient cycling. - Rotation is not only about feed use; it is also a fertility and biology program. - The farm should be read as an interacting system, not a set of separate enterprises.",
    "created_at": "2026-04-13T04:19:38.815900",
    "embedding_id": "knowledge_joel-salatin_02_actionable-lessons",
    "entry_type": "technique",
