  "knowledge_pasture-bird_02_actionable-lessons": {
    "category": "grazing-management",
    "content": "- Technology is useful when it preserves the core regenerative move rather than substituting for it. - Daily pasture access can be mechanized without abandoning the underlying biological logic. - Operational scale should not force the farm into confinement-style compromises.",
