  "knowledge_richard-perkins_02_actionable-lessons": {
    "category": "grazing-management",
    "content": "- Use the scale of permanence as a planning lens: climate, landform, water, trees, access, infrastructure, animals, soils. - Lightweight, modular systems matter because operational flexibility matters. - The back-end decision process is as important as the visible farm layout.",
